Create EC2 instance in aws with these parameters

01.) EC2 Type - Ubuntu t2.micro

02.) EBS Volume - 30GB

03.) Region - US-EAST-1

01.) Open EC2 instance

02.) Click on Launch instance

03.) Update as ap-south-1

04.) Update name

05.) Update aws os Ubuntu

06.) Update Instance type - t2.micro

07.) Proceed without key pair  

08.) Configure storage - 30GB

09.) Click on Launch instance

10.) Select instance and click on connect

11.) Update connection type - "Connect using EC2 Instance connect"

12.) Click on Connect

13.) Sudo su

14.) Open below url
https://github.com/praveen1994dec/tools_installation_scripts/blob/main/jenkins.sh

15.) Update packages
sudo apt update -y

16.) upgrade packages
sudo apt upgrade -y

17.) Install java to run jenkins
sudo apt install openjdk-17-jre -y

18.) Install jenkins credentials
curl -fsSL https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key | sudo tee \
/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc > /dev/null

19.) Set package manager for jenkins
/etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null

20.) Get jenkins package
echo deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc] \
https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ | sudo tee \

21.) Confirm the above script from below url
https://pkg.origin.jenkins.io/debian-stable/

22.) Update packages
sudo apt-get update -y

23.) install jenkins
sudo apt-get install jenkins -y

24.) Open security of the instance

25.) Click on security groups

26.) 

